sourcesContent: import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import { Container, Typography, Paper, Box } from '@mui/material'; import DonationWidget from './DonationWidget'; import PriceChart from './Chart'; function App() { document.title = "Kaspa Rainbow Chart"; const [priceData, setPriceData] = useState({}); useEffect(() => { fetch('/prices.json') .then((response) => response.json()) .then((data) => { const transformedData = data.map((item) => { return { date: item.date, price: parseFloat(parseFloat(item.price.replace('$', '')).toFixed(7)), }; }); setPriceData(transformedData); }) .catch((error) => console.error('Error fetching the prices data:', error)); }, []); return ( Kaspa Rainbow Chart Price according to the power law Click and drag a region to zoom in. Double click to reset. FAQ 1) What is Kaspa's Power Law? The Kaspa power law is a mathematical relationship between Kaspa's price and time, that allows us to forecast Kaspa's potential future price action based on historical data. The power law is demonstrated by plotting Kaspa's price vs time in a log-log chart, where it appears as a straight line. The only other asset which behaves this way is Bitcoin. 2) How accurate is it? The R² of the linear regression in log-log is 0.95. Meaning the power law accounts for 95% of the variance in log-prices. For comparison, the R² of Bitcoin is 0.96. 3) How is this calculated? Support price is calculated as 10^-13.41344198 * (ΔGB)^4.218461. Resistance price is calculated as 10^-13.10611888 * (ΔGB)^4.218461. Fair price is calculated as 10^-13.25978043 * (ΔGB)^4.218461. Where ΔGB is days since the Kaspa Genesis Block, the 7th of November, 2021. [Power Law Equations Updated 2024-07-22] 4) Where can I learn more about Kaspa? Visit the Kaspa project's website: https://kaspa.org. Check out streamlit's Kaspa rainbow chart: https://kasping.streamlit.app/. Marvel at the growth of Kaspa's hash rate: https://2miners.com/kas-network-hashrate. See Kaspa block-DAG processed in real time: https://kgi.kaspad.net/. Check out the Kaspa Industrial Initiative: https://kaspa-kii.org/. 5) How can I buy Kaspa? I use the Tangem wallet (https://amzn.to/3W2Kp4Q) to exchange BTC to KAS through the integrated swap, but you should do your own research to find the best option depending on your country and preferences. I like using Tangem though since it provides cold storage for my Kaspa as well as backup cards. Note, the link above is an Amazon affiliate link which provides me a small percentage which is used to run this website. If you like this website, consider supporting! Want to support this website? If you find this website useful, consider donating some Kaspa. It helps me run the website and build more tools like this. Credit to https://www.blockchaincenter.net/en/bitcoin-rainbow-chart/ for the inspiration for this site. ); } export default App;
